Parliament, Tuesday, 19 January 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Social Development will tomorrow receive a briefing from the Department of Social Development on plans to address challenges pertaining to the lapsing of the temporary disability grants, reapplications, overcrowding at Sassa offices and intervention taken to address the challenges.
	
	Details of the briefing are as follows:
	
	Date: Wednesday, 20 January 2021
	Time: 10h00
	Venue: Zoom platform
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
